The paper deals with object segmentation in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses concepts from object tracking and motion segmentation, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The approach presented in the paper involves combining different sources of information to achieve better segmentation, which is a common theme in machine learning and could place the paper in cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The paper also deals with video processing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics).
